&lt;p&gt;The bank is an ideal way of earning extra money or starting a career in the Trust. It offers work on an ad hoc, flexible basis as you will cover shortages in staffing levels of our permanent staff&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Royal Free and Barnet Critical Care teams are passionate about getting it right for patients and their families. In order to achieve this we are looking to appoint passionate, enthusiastic, motivated and dynamic Bank Band 5 Nurses. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The Royal Free Intensive Care Unit -comprises of 31, level 3 beds, and admits in excess of 1000 patients per year. Specialities at the RFH include Hepato-biliary services, an established liver transplantation programme, haematology, complex vascular surgery, plastic surgery and renal services.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The Barnet Intensive Care unit -comprises of 23 bed, 10 level 2 and 13 level 3. The unit admits in excess of 600 patients per year. Specialities include general medical and surgical patients, patients requiring renal replacement therapies, spinal, plastic and complex lower GI. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We look forward to receiving your application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
